														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3701866">
									

<p>Very cool piece of worldbuilding. Sharp-looking format, too. My own headcanon is inspired by SCP-3989, by FortuneFavorsTheBold, personally:</p>
<p>D vs S vs T- Dimensional, Spatial, Temporal<br />
U vs S vs C vs N- Unstable, Stable, Cycling Stability, Not Known<br />
S vs. M vs. D- Stationary, Mobile, Directed Mobility<br />
U vs. M vs. R- Unaided, Manifested, Ritualistic<br />
WA vs. PA vs. SA vs. AA- Wide Area, Personal Area, Small Area, Alterable Area<br />
S vs H vs C vs U- Safe, Hazardous, Conditional, Uncertain<br />
2 vs. 1 vs. X- 2-Way, 1-Way, Multiple Destinations<br />
C vs. P vs. T vs. G- Cyclic, Permanent, Transient, Generated</p>
<p>So, D-USUWAS2-C would be Dimensional, Unstable, Stationary, Unaided, Wide Area, Safe, 2 way, Cyclic,<br />
S-SMMPAH1-P would be Spatial, Stable, Mobile, Manifested, Personal Area, Hazardous, 1 Way, Permanent, and<br />
T-CDRSAUX-G would be Temporal, Cycling Stability, Directed Mobility, Ritualistic, Small Area, Uncertain Hazard, Multiple Destinations, Generated</p>

